00:30:15.807 --> 00:30:17.890
AUDIENCE: Can I make one
other suggestion, or just

00:30:17.890 --> 00:30:20.090
reinforce one thing
about producing.

00:30:20.090 --> 00:30:21.530
This comes up over
and over again,

00:30:21.530 --> 00:30:24.650
and it was a very hard lesson
for me to learn initially.

00:30:24.650 --> 00:30:27.800
And that's being realistic
about your schedule.

00:30:27.800 --> 00:30:31.090
You know there's a tendency to
want to pack a ton of stuff in

00:30:31.090 --> 00:30:32.480
and to be very ambitious.

00:30:32.480 --> 00:30:35.080
And what happens
is that you have

00:30:35.080 --> 00:30:38.300
to give enough time for setting
things up, breaking things

00:30:38.300 --> 00:30:41.670
down, moving from
this lab to that lab,

00:30:41.670 --> 00:30:43.750
or this location
of that location,

00:30:43.750 --> 00:30:47.430
eating something,
figuring something out.

00:30:47.430 --> 00:30:49.069
So if you go like, well, OK.

00:30:49.069 --> 00:30:51.360
This is a 10 minute scene,
this will take me 20 minutes

00:30:51.360 --> 00:30:51.860
to edit.

00:30:51.860 --> 00:30:54.960
And then we'll be over at Stata,
and we'll shoot that two minute

00:30:54.960 --> 00:30:57.019
scene in five minutes.

00:30:57.019 --> 00:30:59.060
You know, very, very
quickly get behind schedule,

00:30:59.060 --> 00:31:00.514
and then the panic sets in.

00:31:00.514 --> 00:31:02.680
It's far better to have a
schedule that's realistic,

00:31:02.680 --> 00:31:04.849
where you really think
about, not just what it's

00:31:04.849 --> 00:31:06.390
going to take to
shoot, but what it's

00:31:06.390 --> 00:31:08.680
going to take to set up,
breakdown, figure stuff

00:31:08.680 --> 00:31:11.360
out, and move.

00:31:11.360 --> 00:31:14.829
And then execute the
schedule in a realistic way

00:31:14.829 --> 00:31:16.870
so you're not panicking,
you're not freaking out,

00:31:16.870 --> 00:31:18.470
you're not calling
people and saying,

00:31:18.470 --> 00:31:20.900
I know I said I would
be at your lab at 3:00

00:31:20.900 --> 00:31:23.150
but I can't get there till
5:00, can you stick around?

00:31:23.150 --> 00:31:24.430
You know, whatever it may be.

00:31:24.430 --> 00:31:26.040
So just be very realistic.

00:31:26.040 --> 00:31:27.950
PROFESSOR: For the
Science Out Loud episodes,

00:31:27.950 --> 00:31:31.620
we allot at least 12 hours
per five minute episode

00:31:31.620 --> 00:31:33.750
in terms of filming
time with the students.

00:31:33.750 --> 00:31:36.960
Now that's a huge number,
