point I will let you guys free.

00:35:15.830 --> 00:35:19.770
Oh, sorry I have
another thing to say.

00:35:19.770 --> 00:35:22.480
The film that
you've seen today--

00:35:22.480 --> 00:35:26.200
the scene that you film today
won't be due until at least

00:35:26.200 --> 00:35:26.700
Tuesday.

00:35:26.700 --> 00:35:28.250
If you need more
time to work on it,

00:35:28.250 --> 00:35:29.809
we can push it to
Wednesday, too.

00:35:29.809 --> 00:35:31.600
And that's because I
really want your focus

00:35:31.600 --> 00:35:33.260
to be on honing the script.

00:35:33.260 --> 00:35:34.900
Because Monday will
be our table read,

00:35:34.900 --> 00:35:37.229
where everyone reads their
script aloud to each other.

00:35:37.229 --> 00:35:39.020
And you're really going
to get the most out

00:35:39.020 --> 00:35:42.650
of the table read when you
come to it with as complete

00:35:42.650 --> 00:35:44.690
as a script as you can.

00:35:44.690 --> 00:35:46.950
I'm not saying that
what you have on Monday

00:35:46.950 --> 00:35:49.710
should be as close to
final product as possible,

00:35:49.710 --> 00:35:53.770
but it's just really hard
to give concrete feedback

00:35:53.770 --> 00:35:56.320
to something that isn't
fully fleshed out.

00:35:56.320 --> 00:36:01.710
So do try to come on Monday
with as complete of a script

00:36:01.710 --> 00:36:04.210
as you can, because Monday is
going to be the most useful

00:36:04.210 --> 00:36:05.800
to you if you do.

00:36:05.800 --> 00:36:07.800
So that being said,
some people have already

00:36:07.800 --> 00:36:09.940
uploaded second
drafts onto Tumblr.

00:36:09.940 --> 00:36:13.520
If you could upload stuff
by tomorrow at noon,

00:36:13.520 --> 00:36:17.370
I can give you feedback on it
so that you can incorporate that

00:36:17.370 --> 00:36:19.320
before Monday.

00:36:19.320 --> 00:36:22.600
And the best way to
get feedback from me

00:36:22.600 --> 00:36:27.280
is to double post to Tumblr, and
then also write a Google doc,

00:36:27.280 --> 00:36:31.500
and just email it to me, and
give me commenting permissions.

00:36:31.500 --> 00:36:35.010
That's how we actually
edit all the scripts

00:36:35.010 --> 00:36:36.660
from Science Out Loud.

00:36:36.660 --> 00:36:41.788
So I'll show you, real quick.

00:36:46.000 --> 00:36:47.236
Season two.

00:36:51.570 --> 00:36:55.736
Let's go to this one.

